30/08/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- A formal ceremony Monday (29 August) marked the completion of integrated border management reform in Macedonia. 
Police took control of the last remaining border section -- the western border with Albania -- from the army, finalising the overall transfer process launched in the spring of 2004. 
Senior government and army officials, representatives of the EU, OSCE and foreign diplomatic missions in Macedonia attended the ceremony. 
(Macedonian Government Web site - 30/08/05; Makfax, A1 TV - 29/08/05)
